SUMMARY: "Fiber Feast" Exhibition by Martina Celerin
DESCRIPTION:Join us at Pillar Arts By Hand this April as we feature Fiber
  Feast\, a thoughtful curation of 3D woven pieces by Martina Celerin.\n\n
 She's a Bloomington-based artist whose work blends science\, nature\, and
  storytelling through intricate woven forms. Originally trained in plant 
 sciences\, she transitioned to art to explore texture\, color\, and mater
 ial more deeply\, using a mix of fibers and found objects to create richl
 y layered\, tactile pieces inspired by both the natural world and persona
 l experience.\n\nThis exhibition will be on display from Wednesday\, Apri
 l 1-Saturday\, April 25! Don't forget to stop by on Friday\, April 3 from
  5-8 pm for the artist reception for this month's Gallery Walk. Come to m
 eet with the artist\, connect with the arts community\, and enjoy light r
 efreshments.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Exhibition,Free,In-Person,Visual-Arts
