SUMMARY: Art as Inquiry: A Show of Climate Art
DESCRIPTION:All ages are invited to view and explore “Art as Inquiry http
 s://%20https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/climate-co-lab/ \,” a
  juried climate‑art exhibition at the Pillar Arts Alliance Center\, Bloom
 ington\, IN\, from Apr 2–29.\n\nFeaturing 2‑D and 3‑D artworks from 25 ar
 tists across several states\, “Art as Inquiry” invites visitors to encoun
 ter climate research and climate unease\, ecological change\, and environ
 mental justice through the lens of artistic imagination. Beginning April 
 19\, six more artworks from the Climate Co‑lab https://artistsforclimatea
 wareness.org/event/reception-climate-co-lab/ (organized by Brushes for a 
 Better Planet https://lalithashan10.wixsite.com/brushes-for-a-better ) jo
 in the exhibition\, displayed alongside the Art as Inquiry works.\n\nApri
 l 12\, 2–3 pm – Nature Walk https://artistsforclimateawareness.org/event/
 nature-walk-4-12-2026/ \, a pre-reception musical and narrative performan
 ce led by IU Jacobs School of Music student Thejas Mirle https://www.yout
 ube.com/channel/UCNYV1Gj6BS4EDhp17-WFVbA and four composers\, with narrat
 ion by Distinguished IU Biology Professor Roger Hangarter https://www.rog
 erhangarter.net/about .\n\nApril 12\, 3–5 pm – Reception https://artistsf
 orclimateawareness.org/event/art-as-inquiry-reception/ for this member cl
 imate‑art exhibition\; refreshments\; prizes awarded. All welcome.\n\nApr
 il 19\, 3–6 pm – Climate Co‑lab Reception + Nature Walk https://artistsfo
 rclimateawareness.org/event/reception-climate-co-lab/ performance\; brief
  introductions of artists and partners. Refreshments\; all welcome.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Gallery,Visual-Arts
