SUMMARY: The Poison Book Project: The Hidden Hazard on Your Bookshelves
DESCRIPTION:Join us at IU Libraries Lilly Library on Wednesday\, April 22
 \, 2026 for the annual Ruth C. Engs Lecture on Public Health. We are exci
 ted to welcome this year’s speakers\, Dr. Melissa Tedone and Dr. Rosie Gr
 ayburn\, Lead Conservator and Conservation Scientist for the Poison Book 
 Project. The speakers will discuss their research focusing on identifying
  potentially toxic pigments used in bookbinding components and how to han
 dle and store potentially toxic collections more safely.\n\nAlong with re
 freshments\, visitors will have the opportunity to explore the history of
  science and healthcare through a hands-on pop-up exhibition of some of t
 he Lilly Library’s renowned historical medical materials.\n\n\nSchedule\n
 \n4:30 p.m.: Pop-up exhibition featuring arsenical books from the Lilly L
 ibrary’s collections as well as materials related to the history of medic
 ine and public health\n\n5:30 p.m.: “The Poison Book Project: The Hidden 
 Hazard on Your Bookshelves\,” the 2026 Ruth C. Engs lecture\, delivered b
 y Dr. Melissa Tedone and Dr. Rosie Grayburn\n\n6:30 p.m.: Reception and p
 op-up exhibition\n\nSpace is limited\; RSVP now https://events.iu.edu/lib
 raries/event/2259790-engs-lecture-2026-the-poison-book-project !\n\n
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Free
