SUMMARY: Femina Natura
DESCRIPTION:Grace/Butedma Gonso is a Buryat-Mongol artist living in rural
  Indiana. She prefers working\n\nin oils with rich colors. Her depictions
  of her cultural heritage and scenes of rural living are\n\nvibrant and e
 xpressive. Nature is her greatest inspiration. She enjoys capturing seaso
 nal\n\nchanges in nature and local farm and garden images.\n\n\n‘’I mainl
 y paint nature scenes\, avoiding the details as details can be tedious. S
 o most of my\n\npaintings are wide\, expansive\, open views of landscape 
 with certain moods and atmospheres\n\nthat I try to depict. I enjoy putti
 ng down rhythmic\, repeated brush strokes that come out\n\nfreely through
  my intuition.\n\n\nHOWEVER\, every once in a while I paint something dif
 ferent. An event\, a dream\, a movie\, a\n\nbook or a quote would seed an
  idea that results in an abstract\, narrative painting. They tend to\n\na
 ppear somewhat somber\, perhaps expressions of a mother’s fear and worry 
 and a helpless\n\nfeeling towards the future of all living things. We kno
 w that we caused much destruction to\n\nthe planet\, Mother Earth\, our o
 nly vessel on which we all travel through the void.\n\nThis is a show of 
 these paintings.’’\n\n\n
CATEGORIES:Gallery,Exhibition,Free
