SUMMARY: The Writers Guild at Bloomington: First Sunday Prose Reading Lis
 a Kwong and Ellen Wu
DESCRIPTION:May's First Sunday Prose Reading Series is celebrating Asian 
 American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month. Featured readers will be Li
 sa Kwong Ellen Wu. Open mic to follow!\n\nA native of Radford\, Virginia\
 , Lisa Kwong is AppalAsian\, an Affrilachian Poet\, and author of Becomin
 g AppalAsian (Glass Lyre Press) and a Weatherford Award in Poetry nominee
 . Her poetry and creative nonfiction have appeared in The Southern Poetry
  Anthology\, Volume III: Contemporary Appalachia (Second Edition)\; Untel
 ling Magazine\, Women Speak\, A Literary Field Guide to Southern Appalach
 ia\, Pine Mountain Sand & Gravel\, Anthology of Appalachian Writers\, Sti
 ll: The Journal\, Best New Poets\, Appalachian Heritage\, Pluck!\, and ot
 her publications. She is currently working on her second book of poems an
 d a memoir.\n\nEllen Wu is Associate Professor of History at Indiana Univ
 ersity Bloomington. She is author of The Color of Success: Asian American
 s and the Origins of the Model Minority and Overrepresented: The Surprisi
 ng History of Asian Americans and Racial Justice (both from Princeton Uni
 versity Press). Wu’s research and writing has been featured in a variety 
 of platforms\, including Bloomington’s Limestone Post\, Slate\, NPR\, Goo
 p\, the comedy show Adam Ruins Everything\, Last Week Tonight with John O
 liver\, and the PBS documentary series Asian Americans.\n\n﻿Come early to
  sign up\, to shop\, and to get a drink and a treat before the event begi
 ns.\n\n
CATEGORIES:Bloomington
X-TKF-FEATURED-IMAGE:https://d3flpus5evl89n.cloudfront.net/62fb9509b27fd5
 06428328ed/69ef80ff17fe0870b8b8b2d4/scaled_1024.jpg
X-TKF-CUSTOM-PREVIEW:May's First Sunday Prose Reading Series is celebrati
 ng Asian American and Pacific Islander Heritage Month. Featured readers w
 ill be Lisa Kwong Ellen Wu. Open...
