SUMMARY: Thursday Music Night!
DESCRIPTION:Juniper celebrates the return of the U-Station Agents to our 
 Janiece Jaffe Legacy Stage after (almost) BLOWING us away earlier this ye
 ar when the band and their audience were directed to Juniper's basement d
 uring the February 19th tornado!\n\nWell\, they'll be back for an encore\
 , and to finish their unfinished set! We're looking forward to a FUN even
 ing of original music and stories.\n\nThe U-Station Agents are a four-pie
 ce Bloomington rock ensemble offering original tunes wrapped into a folky
 /funky listening experience. They consist of Marta Jasicki on vocals and 
 rhythm guitar\; Robert McCormick\, bass\; Steve Plessinger\, lead guitar\
 , vocals\; and Ivan Record\, percussion\, vocals.\n\nThe “Agents” have pl
 ayed extensively in the area over the years\, notably at the legendary Ca
 fé Django where they hosted and produced the Bloomington Short List varie
 ty show from 2011 to 2012.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington
