SUMMARY: Resounding Joy: Beethoven 9 at the MAC
DESCRIPTION:For the first time in our history the Bloomington Symphony Or
 chestra will perform Beethoven’s iconic 9th Symphony. Joined by a 100+ me
 mber community chorus on the stage of Indiana University’s Musical Arts C
 enter (MAC)\, this is sure to be an unforgettable concert experience that
  will also feature a world premiere piece by Daixuan Ai.\n\nParticipating
  choirs include the Bloomington Chamber Singers (Caio Lopes\, director)\,
  Voces Novae (Sue Swaney\, director) and the choir of the Unitarian Unive
 rsalist Church (Sue Swaney\, director)\, as well as individuals from many
  other local choirs. The choirs are all coming together under the directi
 on of Dr. Betsy Burleigh.\n\nSaturday May 16\, 2026\, at the IU Musical A
 rts Center\n6:15pm pre-concert talk\n7:00pm concert\n\nAdults: $25\, Stud
 ents: $12\, Children under 18: Free
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Music,Live,In-Person
