SUMMARY: Sounds From the Black Hole ft. Bubba Fontaine\, Byrdman\, Loops 
 w/ Lather
DESCRIPTION:Live experimental music series\, May 23 features artists from
  Terre Haute\, Indianapolis and Bloomington playing homemade noise boxes\
 , modular synths and costumed harsh noise wackiness.\n\nALL-AGES\n\n$10 +
  FOOD OR DRINK PURCHASE REQUIRED\n\nThis event is funded in part with gra
 nt support from Visit Bloomington.\n\n________________________\n\nBubba F
 ontaine is an American experimental composer\, artist\, and maker from In
 dianapolis\, IN. He holds a Bachelor of Music from Ball State University\
 , and a doctorate in audiology from Indiana\, University Bloomington. He 
 builds noise boxes of his own design\, augmenting their sounds with analo
 g synthesis. The resulting combination of synthetic and organic sounds lo
 op in and out of distinct but amorphous realms.\n\nbubbafontaine.com/ htt
 ps://bubbafontaine.com/\n\nwww.youtube.com/@bubbafontaine1 https://www.yo
 utube.com/@bubbafontaine1\n\n________________________\n\nByrdman - costum
 ed harsh noise from the vocalist and low-frequency guitarist of the bands
  Thlurm and threefiftysmallblock.\n\nthlurm.bandcamp.com/ https://thlurm.
 bandcamp.com/\n\nthreefiftysmallblock.bandcamp.com/ https://threefiftysma
 llblock.bandcamp.com/\n\n________________________\n\nThe show will open w
 ith a cassette loop demonstration by Lather.\n\nlather.bandcamp.com/ http
 s://lather.bandcamp.com/
